  "original_title": "\u0b87\u0bb2\u0b99\u0bcd\u0b95\u0bc8 \u0ba8\u0bc6\u0bb0\u0bc1\u0b95\u0bcd\u0b95\u0b9f\u0bbf \u0bae\u0ba9\u0bbf\u0ba4 \u0b89\u0bb0\u0bbf\u0bae\u0bc8\u0b95\u0bb3\u0bcd \u0bae\u0bc0\u0ba4\u0bc1 \u0ba4\u0bbe\u0b95\u0bcd\u0b95\u0ba4\u0bcd\u0ba4\u0bc8 \u0b8f\u0bb1\u0bcd\u0baa\u0b9f\u0bc1\u0ba4\u0bcd\u0ba4\u0bc1\u0b95\u0bbf\u0ba9\u0bcd\u0bb1\u0ba4\u0bc1 - \u0b90\u0ba8\u0bbe \u0ba8\u0bbf\u0baa\u0bc1\u0ba3\u0bb0\u0bcd",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "Sri Lanka Crisis Impacts Human Rights - UN Expert",
      "author": "Rajeeban",
      "body_lines": [
        "United Nations experts have expressed concern over rising inflation, rising commodity prices, fuel shortages, electricity shortages, and an economic downturn in Sri Lanka.",
        "UN Special Expert on Foreign Debt and Human Rights, Attia Waris, said that the crisis Sri Lanka is facing has also had a great impact on the enjoyment of human rights by the country's people.",
        "He stated that we have repeatedly seen the bad effects of the debt crisis on countries, he said that the debt crisis has exposed the deep structural gaps of the global financial system and has also affected the implementation of human rights.",
        "He mentioned that human rights should be seen as the basis of any attempt to find a solution to the economic crisis and the context of negotiations with the International Monetary Fund should be seen as such.",
        "He also mentioned that in the report released after visiting Sri Lanka in 2019, UN experts pointed out the increasing structural debt and in that report, the country's biggest expenditure is debt expenditure.",
        "He said that Sri Lanka's downfall should immediately attract the attention of the world, not only humanitarian organizations, but also international financial institutions, private lenders and other countries should come forward to help Sri Lanka."
      ],
